THE Germiston-based Hawks’ serious corruption investigation team, assisted by police officers from Vhulaudzi cop shop in Limpopo, arrested a 46-year-old former sergeant for corruption. She appeared in the Dzanani Magistrates Court on Wednesday, 20 July, and the matter was transferred to the Palm Ridge Specialised Commercial Crimes Court. Warrant Officer Bonnie Nxumalo said it is alleged that in 2016, the suspect approached a complainant whose car was impounded and demanded R12 000 to release it.   It was paid but the bakkie wasn’t released. In 2017, she allegedly demanded R6 000 from a taxi driver to “squash” a docket. It was paid but the owner reported the matter. She was arrested on Tuesday, 19 July.